MAP EDITING
-----------
To use the map editing feature, set mode = 'edit' rather than 'play'

Left-click......Small Selection Brush
Right-click.....Large Selection Brush
c...............Edit Colour
r...............Raise Selection
l...............Lower Selection
x...............Export Map
p...............Load Previously Exported Map
k...............Colour Selection quickly with previously selected colour
s...............Input two colours, it will colour all flat tiles the first colour, and other tiles the second colour

Colours are in the form
r,g,b
ranging from 0 to 255
You can use a capital X in place of a number to generate a random number (180-220) for each tile coloured,
creating a variance effect
